ðŸ“Œ Problem Statement
Predict the price of a house based on its size using Machine Learning.


ðŸ“¥ Input Data

The input data for this problem consists of the size of the house measured in square feet.
Example Input:
800 sq ft
1200 sq ft

ðŸ“¥ Expected Output

The expected output of the Machine Learning model is the predicted price of the house.
Example Output:
â‚¹25,00,000
â‚¹45,00,000


ðŸ”¹ Workflow for House Price Prediction

1. Define the problem:
   Predict house prices using house size.
2. Collect data:
   Gather data containing house sizes and their prices.
3. Preprocess data:
   Clean the data and remove missing values.
4. Select model:
   Choose a simple regression model.
5. Train model:
   Train the model using historical data.
6. Evaluate model:
   Check accuracy using test data.
7. Make prediction:
   Predict the price of a new house.
